field_data.Author: Scott
field_data.Sample Name: Yang1 is 10 ug IrO2 powder on GC, Rao1F is 2 ug hydrous RuO2 powder on GC, Melih1 is 25nm Ru sputtered at 400C on 5nm Ti on GC
field_data.Removed from vacuum: nanoparticles dropcast last night and dried since, Melih1 sputtered yesterday.

notes: Air signal had been high, so took of chip and replaced center o-ring. Drop-test now looks good. Ezra mounted sample. ------ Yang1 ------ Yang1 shows very little activity, went to higher overpotential, some OER but then electrode dies. ------- Rao1H ------- Good activity on first cycle, but less each subsequent cycle. Nanoparticles not stable. Brian Knudsen told me inks are hard. I don't have time for hard things. ------ Melih1 ------- I forgot how much I love metals. Great H region, Great CO stripping. CO adsorption transient is negative, even in H region! Very broad CO strip. Did it four times at various dosing potentials. Capacitance looks similar to Rehma4B, perhaps not surprising since they were sputtered at the same temperature. Great at ORR. 01... Okay, I want to try an O strip as the first thing at OER potential with this guy. ORR onset as at 0.9 V vs RHE. Okay, first I'm going to try CO O exchange. Gonna hold at 0.9 V vs RHE. No luck. The same m/z=44 transient as always which is equal to that in the second control. It's exchange, but in the vacuum chamber. Neither does the OER O stripping experiment show anything. 02... Film looks surprisingly stable. It actually looks exactly like one of the RuO2 films, just very low-capacity. Since I have a CO strip on this one, I have a calibration for the capacity :D ... Hard to overstate that success. If only I can find a value for the CO coverage of Ru. Like Ir, though, it seems to have a "bulk memory" thing going. THe more oxidative the OER step, the more cathodic current during the pause at 1.2 V vs RHE. 03... Setting it to run overnight with one-hour pulses, since it looks completely beautifully stable over the 2-minute pulses. Ran fine overnight! Looks stable. Tried CO stripping after, got one, with 5 mV/s, at 72500 s, but didn't wait long enough after dosing CO. Messed up a bit in EC-lab after that. 04... new file. CO stripping at 20 mV/s. Interingly, about same CO stripping area despite much larger capacitance (comparing to 01...), no more CO adsorption transient.
